column5: You think Im going to answer that here,out in the open?  There was a guy in a kyak in the marina. Maybe it was BillM.LOL

I took mine out of hiding two days ago. Took the tarp off earlier today to check for winter damage. NONE! She's going in on Friday for a new custom tarp. Now I need to find a good place to buy 3 galvanized trailer wheels. These regular wheels keep looking rusty. Oh, also want to mount the spare on a hub as an extra.

I took a drive to Orillia this morning to get my derby tag, the Simcoe side is almost open all the way, just a bit of ice on the East side of the Narrows.  The free launch is open although the dock has not been installed.  The water level is a bit higher, the cement pad is completely under water.  On the Couchiching side there's a bit more ice but that will probably go in the next week.  Took a walk down the old rail bed, surprised that nobody was fishing there.  On the way back, saw 2 boats being launched at the free launch.
Yer not going to do, what Im thinking yer going to do???????????????  Looking forward to the new wrap Roy.
i launched the boat at tiffin this afternoon and went for a rip.   got some good perch while we were at it!   ice went out quick!
Ice did go out quick. I will be tout there sometime this week I hope.
Just checked the forecast and I think my boat will stay wraped for a while yet.
I'm hoping to "springerize" mine next weekend...
Glad to hear the launch  is open.That concrete ramp is just about useless. Seen more people get hung up when they drop thier trailer wheels off the end or worse yet one of the side!.  TB
Yea i've always launch to the left of the concrete launch way better

Get the boat out?  I've been on the water for the last three weeks.  Didn't catch anything (till yesterday).  Caught this nice 8 lbs beast using an ultra light rod and lure going after perch.  Had no fight whatso ever.  Felt like a bunch of weeds coming in.  Water is 36 deg.

I have been out in my boat three times already crappie fishing. All three days were fantastic days weather wise and two were FANTASTIC fishing wise. The first day we couldn't find any active crappie but caught a LOT of perch. The last two we loaded up on the crappies. Good Friday will be enjoyed with the best eating fish out.......

yup rebuilt the livewell flappers, replaced the bilge and two livewell pumps, installed new colour bird on the front deck, replaced waterpump impeller, greased motor pivot shaft, just need to vacuum carpet and service trailer and all ready to go
